Confluence's xwork.xml file declares the params interceptor before the autowire interceptor. This was done for good reasons a long time ago.  It prevents methods on dependencies being deliberately or accidentally called using inappropriate request parameters.

That problem was solved more thoroughly by CONF-13056 in Confluence 2.10, so it is now possible to safely reorder them.

This would be extremely beneficial, since it would allow us to better componentise the actions in a spring-friendly way.  State and Behaviour could be happily delegated to ActionHelpers used by different Actions that don't extend each other but share commonalities.  This is currently infeasible without retrieving things directly from the ContainerManager.  Similarly painful is the inability of parameter setting methods to transform IDs to objects by calling methods on dependencies.

