Currently, we use the pattern: 

{code}+myVariable{code}

Which is the shortcut we use to ensure that {{myVariable = "0"}} is considered falsy.

In all the current places this pattern is used, we do not use the subsequent result for any arithmetic. But we do not want to encourage this use given that some very old Confluence instances can have content ID's that exceed 15-16 digits, where doing so will lead to a loss of precision and bugs like: CONF-17739.

Also see: http://www.jibbering.com/faq/#binaryNumbers

We should introduce a method like {{isValidContentId}} that returns false for "0" in addition to true for string values with positive numbers.

