As part of a blitz test on QA-EAC, I found that PowerPoint 2007 files do not display on a page when using IE 7 (when using the Macromedia Flash Player 6 plugin). Ryan A confirmed this.

Hence, please show a helpful error message in the space used to show the PPTX file on a page.

For example:

{quote}Your browser's current Flash Player add-on version does not support the display of this Office file in Confluence. Please upgrade your browser's Flash Player add-on to at least version 9.
{quote}

Also, if it's only the Adobe Flash Player add-on that's supported, then reword this message to:

{quote}Your browser's current Flash Player add-on version does not support the display of this Office file in Confluence. Please upgrade your browser's Flash Player add-on to at least Adobe Flash Player version 9.
{quote}

NB - Early versions of the Flash Player were called *Macromedia Flash Player* - hence, this choice of wording.

